               <floruit>616<ref type="note" corresp="#d2e22097"/>
               </floruit>
               <note xml:id="d2e22067" n="1"> In Syriac, see vol.
                                4, Introduction 2.8.1, pp. 18-9. In Hebrew this would read יונא. On
                                the replacement of the ה suffix with א see vol. 1, Introduction
                                2.4.2.7, p.
                        26.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e22073" n="2"> The text speaks of the forced conversion of Jews (ܝܗܘܵܕܝܐ). He is
                                described as ܚܕ ܡܢܗܘܢ ܡܢ ܪܝܵܫܐ ܕܒܗܘܢ (one of them, one of their
                                leaders) and is their spokesman.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e22090" n="3"> See previous note, and Introduction
                            5.1.1.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e22097" n="4"> This is the date at
                                which time this information is inserted in the chronicle (928 of the
                                Seleucid era, see Introduction 7.5.4.1).</note>
